<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-05-11T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-05-11T17:00:00-05:00" n="702" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d702">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/525: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">White</hi></persName>)<note n="27" xml:id="d702fn27">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                                        mutandis</hi>, on the same date to the Ambassador in Brazil
                                    as telegram No. 15.</note></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-11T18:00:00-04:00">May 11, 1929—6
                                    p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>37. Formal action is to be taken May 13 by the Commission of Inquiry
                                and Conciliation, Bolivia and Paraguay, with regard to the
                                repatriation of prisoners. The plan will probably call for the
                                services of the Military Attaché at your mission. Please ask him to
                                be ready.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>